Observation Details: A loose group of small ducks having black heads (some with crowns) grey-black bills (some with distinct white stripes) grey-brown wings, and short, pin-like tails (some black, some brown on top).  Generally uniform appearance - no obvious separation by gender.  At rest, floating in the water.  No dabbling or diving.  One preening / bathing.
Mostly adult males.  All had the distinctive white/grey patterned bills.

Observation Details: We watched from the boardwalk as a pair of ducks flew in for a landing on the ocean near a small group maybe 800 feet out from the beach.  They were too distant to identify by 10x binoculars, so I'm relying completely on the photos, and hoping that I have not made a misidentification.  Apologies for the poor quality of the photos - it was cloudy and my camera is less than top-of-the-line.
